{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Hosted Lean proof: plby proof of 202 (state complete) https://github.com/plby/lean-proofs/blob/main/src/v4.29.1/ErdosProblems/Erdos202.lean.","id":"vf_38741ac080ee244d","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #202: declared status 'solved'. Formalized: no. Let $n_1<\\cdots < n_r\\leq N$ with associated $a_i\\pmod{n_i}$ such that the congruence classes are disjoint (that is, every integer is $\\equiv a_i\\pmod{n_i}$ for at most one $1\\leq i\\leq r$). How large can $r$ be in terms of $N$? Current best: Erd\\H{o}s believed the lower bound is closer to the truth. These bounds were further improved by Chen \\cite{Ch05} and then by de la Bret\\'{e}che, Ford, and Vandehey \\cite{BFV13} to\\[\\frac{N}{L(N)^{1+o(1)}}<f(N) < \\frac{N}{L(N)^{\\sqrt{3}/2+o(1)}}.\\]The latter authors conjecture that the lower bound here is the truth. Prize: no. OEIS: A389975. Tags: covering systems.","id":"vf_9ec551f1a5a2682d","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Hosted Lean proof: jayyhk proof of 202 (state complete) https://github.com/Jayyhk/erdos-lean/blob/main/problems/202/Erdos202.lean.","id":"vf_b44c8b43e8b255c5","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Full solution.","id":"vf_f83213ba836802c0","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"claim":"Pinned Formal Conjectures activity classification; integration activity does not establish mathematical truth.","id":"activity:fc-proof_link_edit:202","kind":"proof_link_edit","lifecycle":"banked","source_ref":"sources/formal-conjectures-activity.yaml#problem-202","trust":"declared"}],"activity_types":["proof_link_edit"],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[{"commit":"8f6648ff0fbd771db53859cd436d37a8d6a68a57","repository":"formal_conjectures","source_root":"sha256:6d0afbf6609d6c019d2d8c3cc13bcbe5c8de6d5573e9322ca4e94be2c98a2928"}],"dependency_impact":"problem_lo